        <p>
          QUANTA is a decentralized portfolio-based alpha signal generation network on Bittensor. Talented stock pickers exist globally—retail traders, quantitative researchers, AI/ML engineers—but they have no trustworthy way to prove skill or monetize it. Traditional trading competitions reward lucky gamblers who take maximum risk, and the equities market remains gatekept by hedge funds requiring credentials, connections, and capital.
        </p>
        <p>
          QUANTA runs a continuous, permissionless stock picking competition. Participants submit portfolio signals consisting of ticker-weight allocations, and validators score them using real market data and risk-adjusted metrics that measure whether returns justify the risk taken to achieve them. Unlike competitions that reward raw returns, QUANTA rewards consistency and risk management across rolling evaluation windows.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Signal Pool architecture enables unlimited participation through retail-friendly methods—web applications, APIs, webhooks—while sophisticated participants can deploy fully automated bespoke strategies. Everything in between is welcome. Because signals are scored against real market data but never execute real trades, there's no fund management complexity—pure simulation with real performance tracking.
        </p>
        <p>
          QUANTA is where traders and data scientists compete on equal footing. Students building their first algorithmic strategy, retail traders testing discretionary picks, and professional quants running production systems can all integrate QUANTA into their existing workflows. The resulting consensus signal—aggregated from thousands of independently validated strategies—creates actionable intelligence for real-world allocation.
        </p>
